# Supabase Row Level Security (RLS)

Every Supabase table that stores third-party data **must** have Row Level Security enabled with at least one policy before any application code reads from or writes to it.

## Tables in scope

### Phase 2 — Outreach LimaLeads

| Table            | Data stored                          |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `companies`      | Apollo-imported company records      |
| `contacts`       | Apollo-imported contact records      |
| `leads`          | Pipeline entries per contact         |
| `sequences`      | Email sequence definitions           |
| `sequence_runs`  | Per-lead sequence execution state    |
| `messages`       | Sent/drafted email messages          |
| `templates`      | Reusable email templates             |
| `reminders`      | Follow-up reminders per lead         |
| `ai_logs`        | Gemini call logs (tokens, cost, etc) |

### Phase 3 — Client Portal

| Table             | Data stored                           |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `accounts`        | Client accounts                       |
| `account_members` | Users belonging to an account         |
| `projects`        | Projects scoped to an account         |
| `milestones`      | Project milestones                    |
| `deliverables`    | Files and links per milestone         |
| `comments`        | Threaded comments on deliverables     |
| `intake_forms`    | Client onboarding intake responses    |

## Migration checklist

When creating a migration that adds any of the above tables, always include:

```sql
alter table <table_name> enable row level security;

-- At minimum, a restrictive default (deny all):
create policy "deny all by default" on <table_name>
  as restrictive
  for all
  using (false);
```

Then add the real access policies required by the feature.

## Enforcement

If a PR creates a new table in scope without RLS enabled, block the PR and request the migration to be updated before merging.
